cleanContent: JIUQUAN, Oct. 31 (Xinhua) -- A China manned space program spokesperson said here Monday that China is going to conduct another manned space mission by 2012.Spokeswoman Wu Ping said at a press briefing Monday morning that China plans to launch in 2012 spaceships Shenzhou-9 and Shenzhou-10, which are expected to dock with China's first space lab module, Tiangong-1."At least one mission of the two will be manned," Wu said.																																																																								|  |
